---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import KusadasiInfo from '~/components/widgets/AroundInfoFeatures.astro';
import Hero from '~/components/widgets/Hero.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '~/components/widgets/breadcrumb.astro';
import Layout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import { ViewTransitions } from 'astro:transitions';
import photo from 'src/assets/images/izmir.jpg';
import photo2 from 'src/assets/images/izmir2.jpg';
import photo3 from 'src/assets/images/izmir3.jpg';
import BrakePad from 'astro-vtbot/components/BrakePad.astro';
import ProgressBar from 'astro-vtbot/components/ProgressBar.astro';




const metadata = {
  title: 'Izmir',
};
---
<ProgressBar />
{/* To observe the effect in DEV mode it is necessary to simulate 2000ms loading time */}
<BrakePad duration={2000} />

<Layout metadata={metadata}>
  <ViewTransitions />
  <!-- Hero Widget ******************* -->

  <Hero
    tagline=""
    title="Izmir"
    subtitle="Discovering Izmir: A Traveler's Paradise"
    image={{
      src: photo,
      alt: 'Izmir',
    }}
  />

  <!-- Features2 Widget ************** -->
  <section class="px-4 md:px-6 py-2 sm:py-2 lg:py-2 mx-auto max-w-4xl">

<p class="text-base">


</p> 



<br>

<p class="text-base">
  Nestled along the stunning Aegean coastline of Turkey lies Izmir, a
   vibrant metropolis brimming with history, culture, and endless opportunities for exploration.
    As Turkey's third-largest city, Izmir offers travelers a captivating blend of ancient landmarks,
     bustling bazaars, and picturesque seaside promenades, making it a must-visit destination
      for anyone seeking an unforgettable Turkish adventure.
</p> <br>
<Image src={photo2} alt="Priene" class="rounded-md mb-4"/>
<h2 class="text-2xl font-extrabold dark:text-white">Unraveling Ancient Treasures:</h2>
<p class="text-base">
  History comes to life in Izmir, where ancient ruins and archaeological sites abound.
   Explore the remnants of the ancient city of Smyrna at the Agora of Smyrna, where you
    can wander among the well-preserved columns and structures dating back to the Hellenistic
     period. Don't miss the chance to visit the imposing Kadifekale Castle, perched 
     atop a hill overlooking the city, offering panoramic views of Izmir's skyline and the 
     shimmering waters of the Aegean Sea.
</p> <br>

<h2 class="text-2xl font-extrabold dark:text-white">A Tapestry of Culture and Cuisine</h2>
<p class="text-base">
  Immerse yourself in Izmir's rich cultural tapestry as you stroll through its vibrant
   neighborhoods and bustling markets. Explore the historic Kemeraltı Bazaar, a labyrinth 
   of narrow streets and alleys brimming with artisanal crafts, colorful textiles, and
    aromatic spices. Indulge your taste buds with Izmir's culinary delights, 
    from freshly caught seafood and savory kebabs to mouthwatering sweets like lokma and künefe,
     all served with warm Turkish hospitality that will leave you craving more.
</p> <br>
<Image src={photo3} alt="Priene" class="rounded-md mb-4"/>

<h2 class="text-2xl font-extrabold dark:text-white">Seaside Serenity and Coastal Charms</h2>
<p class="text-base">
  For a tranquil escape from the city bustle, head to the nearby coastal towns of 
  Çeşme and Alaçatı, renowned for their pristine beaches, azure waters, and charming
   cobblestone streets. Spend your days basking in the Mediterranean sun,
    exploring ancient windmills, or indulging in a leisurely meal at a seaside taverna,
    where you can savor the freshest seafood and admire breathtaking sunsets over the horizon.


</p> <br>

<p class="text-base">
  From its ancient ruins and bustling bazaars to its tranquil beaches and culinary delights, 
  Izmir offers travelers a diverse array of experiences just waiting to be discovered.
   Whether you're wandering through its historic streets, sampling local delicacies, 
   or simply soaking in the coastal beauty, Izmir invites you to embark on an unforgettable 
   journey through Turkey's cultural heartland.


</p> <br>





    </section>


    <KusadasiInfo />
  
  <!-- Breadcrumb -->


  <Breadcrumb firstText="Around Kusadasi" firstLink="/misc" title={metadata.title} />

</Layout>
